# Backtester Frontend Patterns

## Color Palette (match app exactly)
- Background: `bg-[#f7f8fb]` (main), `bg-white` (cards), `bg-slate-50` (headers)
- Borders: `border-slate-200/80`
- Text: `text-slate-800` (primary), `text-slate-600` (secondary), `text-slate-400` (tertiary)
- Accents: `text-indigo-600`, `bg-indigo-500`, `bg-indigo-50`
- Positive: `text-emerald-600`, `bg-emerald-50`
- Negative: `text-red-500`, `bg-red-50`
- Font sizes: `text-[10px]` to `text-[13px]`
- No emojis in UI

## Performance Rules
- Virtualize trade logs with `react-virtuoso` (unlimited trades)
- Lazy load Plotly charts with `next/dynamic` + `ssr: false`
- Memoize all sub-components with `React.memo`
- Use `useMemo` for derived computations (metrics formatting, color coding)
- Tab panels should only render their active content

## Backtest Result Types
- Mirror Python Pydantic models in `BacktestTypes.ts`
- BacktestResult contains: strategy, core_metrics, advanced_metrics, walk_forward, monte_carlo, trades, equity_curve, drawdown_curve, monthly_returns

## Slash Command System
- Triggered by `/` in chat input
- Keyboard navigable (arrows + enter)
- Extensible command registry (add new commands without modifying menu)
- Commands define: id, label, description, category, template
